Description: Fragment of flattened handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine buff-brown.
Production date: 137 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Name Thersandros. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABV 0138.08. Probably same as Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 96, 7
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1091)
